 <H1>Problems with Decompositions</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>There are three potential problems to consider:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI> Some queries become more expensive.  
<UL>
<LI>e.g.,  How much did sailor Joe earn?  (salary = W*H)
</UL><LI> Given instances of the decomposed relations, we may not be able to reconstruct the corresponding instance of the original relation!  
<UL>
<LI>Fortunately, not in the SNLRWH example.
</UL><LI> Checking some dependencies may require joining the instances of the decomposed relations.
<UL>
<LI>Fortunately, not in the SNLRWH example.
</UL></UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Tradeoff:   Must consider these issues vs. redundancy.</H2>
</UL></P>
